sec.p:
A total of eight groundwater samples were collected from seven boreholes (BH1, BH2, BH3, BH4, BH5, BH6, and BH7) and one hand-dug well (WL3) located in Egbeagu Amansea. The boreholes and the well were purged by pumping water for 5–10 minutes to ensure representative groundwater was collected. Sterile 1-liter polyethylene bottles were rinsed with the groundwater to be sampled before collection. Two sets of samples were collected at each point: One for physicochemical analysis (pH, electrical conductivity (EC), total dissolved solids (TDS), total hardness, carbonate, fluoride, nitrate, sulphate, and chloride) and another for cation analysis (calcium, potassium, sodium, and magnesium). Samples for cation analysis were acidified with 2–3 drops of concentrated nitric acid (HNO



      3


) to a pH $<$ 2 to preserve metal ions. Samples were labelled with identification number, date, and time, and stored in a portable cooler at 4 °C for analysis within 24–48 hours to minimize degradation.

